# ─── Audit / legal / sensitive documentation — never commit ───────
# These are internal working documents (security audits we ran against
# our own build, defect checklists for the corporate parent site,
# legal-consultation notes, draft notice letters, post-cutover write-
# ups). They contain data we don't want public — defects we found,
# legal posture, and our internal vulnerability counts. The corporate
# handoff PROPOSAL is intentionally excluded from the gitignore so it
# stays in the repo.
docs/security/external-domain-audit-*
docs/security/post-cutover-report-*
docs/security/wavemaxlaundry-site-audit-*
docs/security/wavemax-promo-prelaunch-audit-*
docs/security/parent-site-fix-checklist.*
docs/security/parent-site-footer-defects-checklist.*
docs/security/parent-site-user-testing-checklist.*
docs/security/draft-23-20-notice-letter.*
docs/security/lawyer-consultation-*
docs/security/lawyer-intake-form-*
docs/corporate-handoff/code-quality-comparison-*
